  '<h2 id="threat-catalog">Threat catalog <a class="anchor" href="#threat-catalog">#</a></h2>',
  '<ul>',
  '<li><strong>RFC 1035 length caps</strong> — labels exceed 63 octets or full name exceeds 253 octets. Resolvers truncate or refuse inconsistently; downstream parsers panic. Refused regardless of profile (length is structural).</li>',
  '<li><strong>LDH rule (RFC 952 / 1123)</strong> — letters / digits / hyphens; no leading or trailing hyphen on a label; no <code>--</code> at positions 3-4 unless <code>xn--</code> IDN prefix. Underscores forbidden in hostnames (only allowed as RFC 8552 service-discovery prefixes).</li>',
  '<li><strong>IDN homograph / mixed-script confusables</strong> (RFC 5891-5894 IDNA2008, UTS #39) — Cyrillic / Greek / Cherokee / Armenian / Han / Hiragana / Katakana / Hangul / Arabic / Hebrew codepoints mixed with Latin in a single label. Strict allows Latin only; balanced allows the major international scripts; permissive allows every script with a warn-only audit.</li>',
  '<li><strong>BIDI / RTL override</strong> (CVE-2021-42574 Trojan Source) — U+202A-202E / U+2066-2069 / U+200E / U+200F embedded in labels reorder visual presentation in address bars / log lines / audit records. Refused at every profile (a domain with hostile BIDI is forged, not malformed).</li>',
  '<li><strong>Zero-width / format codepoints</strong> — U+200B-200D / U+FEFF / U+2060 / U+00AD split a visible label into two parsed labels or hide characters. Refused at every profile (universal invisible-label-segmentation defense).</li>',
