  '<li><strong>IPv4-as-domain confusion</strong> (RFC 3986 §3.2.2 + CVE-2021-22931) — dotted-decimal, octal (<code>0177.0.0.1</code>), hex (<code>0xC0.0xA8.0x01.0x01</code>), and long-decimal (<code>3232235777</code>) IPv4 forms accepted by <code>inet_aton</code>-style parsers but compared as strings by allowlist matchers. DNS-rebinding class.</li>',
